Django 2.0 requires python3

Installation Instructions

This document assumes one is using Ubuntu 16.04 LTS


Run the following from the command line

sudo apt-get install python3-pip

pip3 install django

To run the development server move into the source directory

cd ./takehomeinterview/
python3 manage.py runserver

Then visit 127.0.0.1:8000/planets/

To visit the admin page visit 127.0.0.1:8000/admin
username: admin
password: letmeinplease
